mitelRouterPppGroup.contactinfo: Standards Group, Postal: MITEL Corporation 350 Legget Drive, PO Box 13089 Kanata, Ontario Canada K2K 1X3 Tel: +1 613 592 2122 Fax: +1 613 592 4784 E-mail: std@mitel.com

mitelGblGrpNegotiateFirst.name: mitelGblGrpNegotiateFirst
mitelGblGrpNegotiateFirst.description: This attribute defines which PPP authentication protocol is negotiated first on incoming call. DEFAULT = chap

mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAddr.name: mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAddr
mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAddr.description: This attribute defines the start address of the dynamic addres pool.

mitelGblGrpNumDynamicIpAddr.name: mitelGblGrpNumDynamicIpAddr
mitelGblGrpNumDynamicIpAddr.description: This attribute defines the number of dynamic IP addresses in the pool.

mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAdrrHoldoff.name: mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAdrrHoldoff
mitelGblGrpDynamicIpAdrrHoldoff.description: This attribute defines the time in seconds before the same IP address can be reused after a call has been disconnected.

mitelGblGrpRemDnsIpAddrHandling.name: mitelGblGrpRemDnsIpAddrHandling
mitelGblGrpRemDnsIpAddrHandling.description: This attribute determines wether the system can accept or override the DNS IP address submitted by a remote system. DEFAULT = accept. Override has been superceded by overridewith.

mitelGblGrpPrimaryWinsServerIpAddr.name: mitelGblGrpPrimaryWinsServerIpAddr
mitelGblGrpPrimaryWinsServerIpAddr.description: This attribute defines the Primary WINS server IP address of your Network.

mitelGblGrpSecondaryWinsServerIpAddr.name: mitelGblGrpSecondaryWinsServerIpAddr
mitelGblGrpSecondaryWinsServerIpAddr.description: This attribute defines the Secondary WINS server IP address of your Network.

mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigTable.name: mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigTable
mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigTable.description: This table contains objects that pertain to the management of remote LANs that use the PPP Internet standard link protocol.

mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigEntry.name: mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigEntry
mitelPppGrpRemoteConfigEntry.description: A default entry at conceptual row zero does exist in this table. The default entry can be used to specify the PPP authentication protocol only.

mitelRmtCfgTableIndex.name: mitelRmtCfgTableIndex
mitelRmtCfgTableIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies this object

mitelRmtCfgTableIpAddrHandling.name: mitelRmtCfgTableIpAddrHandling
mitelRmtCfgTableIpAddrHandling.description: This attribute determines wether the system can accept or override the DNS IP address submitted by a remote system. DEFAULT = accept.

mitelRmtCfgTableRemIpAddr.name: mitelRmtCfgTableRemIpAddr
mitelRmtCfgTableRemIpAddr.description: The IP address to assign to remote if mitelRmtCfgTableIPAddrHandling is set to assign(3)

mitelRmtCfgTableStatus.name: mitelRmtCfgTableStatus
mitelRmtCfgTableStatus.description: The current status of this entry.

mitelRmtCfgTablePppMode.name: mitelRmtCfgTablePppMode
mitelRmtCfgTablePppMode.description: The mode PPP will be using for the given destination.

mitelPppGrpPppOverEthernetTable.name: mitelPppGrpPppOverEthernetTable
mitelPppGrpPppOverEthernetTable.description: Table containing the configuration items needed by the PPPoE stack.

mitelPppOEthTableIndex.name: mitelPppOEthTableIndex
mitelPppOEthTableIndex.description: Unique Identifier for an entry in PPP over Ethernet Table.

mitelPppOEthTableEnabled.name: mitelPppOEthTableEnabled
mitelPppOEthTableEnabled.description: Is this PPPoE instance enabled or not.

mitelPppOEthTablePacketTimeout.name: mitelPppOEthTablePacketTimeout
mitelPppOEthTablePacketTimeout.description: The time to wait, in seconds, for a valid response to a discovery packet before resending it. Warning: this value is doubled ever time a packet is resent.

mitelPppOEthTablePacketRetries.name: mitelPppOEthTablePacketRetries
mitelPppOEthTablePacketRetries.description: The number of times to resend discovery packets before giving up on the negotiation.

mitelPppOEthTableTotalRetries.name: mitelPppOEthTableTotalRetries
mitelPppOEthTableTotalRetries.description: The RFC states that failure to receive a valid PADS packet should restart the negotiation. This count stops the system retrying indefinitely on duff PADS packets by capping the total number of retry attempts.

mitelPppOEthTableServiceName.name: mitelPppOEthTableServiceName
mitelPppOEthTableServiceName.description: The service we wish to request from the remote access concentrator. Examples of the use of the service name are to indicate an ISP or a class or quality of service. An empty string indicates any service.

mitelPppOEthTableACName.name: mitelPppOEthTableACName
mitelPppOEthTableACName.description: Description of the remote access concentrator we wish to connect to. An empty string indicates no preference.
